-- Colombia Reaches Accord With Air-Traffic Controllers, RCN Says
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-02-20T12:52:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/colombia-reaches-accord-with-air-traffic-controllers-rcn-says.html
Colombia  reached an agreement with
air-traffic controllers last night, putting an end to a labor
dispute that caused flight delays and cancellations in the past
three weeks in the South American country, RCN Radio  said ,
citing Deputy Labor Minister David Luna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
